Objective:

ğŸ”¹ This paper proposes SCHE2MA, a multi-domain, energy-efficient, AI-driven orchestration framework for Beyond-5G (B5G) networks.
ğŸ”¹ It focuses on automating Service Function Chain (SFC) placement while optimizing for:

Ultra-Reliable Low Latency Communication (URLLC) services.

Energy efficiency, reducing operational costs and carbon footprint.
ğŸ”¹ Uses distributed Reinforcement Learning (RL) instead of traditional centralized approaches to scale better and reduce failures.



---

Challenges Addressed:

âœ… Massive Growth in 5G/B5G Services:

More devices, more applications â†’ Networks must scale dynamically.

Traditional manual management is inefficient and costly.


âœ… Need for Intelligent Network Orchestration:

Uses Software-Defined Networking (SDN) and Network Function Virtualization (NFV) to enable automated scaling.

Ensures zero-touch service management with AI-driven decision-making.


âœ… Latency & Energy Efficiency Trade-Off:

URLLC services need ultra-low latency (e.g., self-driving cars, industrial automation).

But keeping resources active increases energy consumption.

SCHE2MA optimizes both latency & energy consumption simultaneously.


âœ… Complexity of Multi-Domain Networks:

Traditional centralized solutions cause bottlenecks and fail as the network grows.

SCHE2MA distributes the decision-making among multiple network domains, making it more scalable and reliable.



---

Optimization Approach:

ğŸ”¸ Distributed Reinforcement Learning (RL) for SFC Placement:

Uses multiple AI agents to make local decisions instead of one central controller.

Scales better and avoids a single point of failure.


ğŸ”¸ Auction Mechanism for Inter-Domain SFC Migration:

Each domain bids for hosting VNFs, ensuring optimized placement based on real-time demand.


ğŸ”¸ Energy-Aware Placement Strategy:

Minimizes unnecessary Virtual Network Function (VNF) migrations, reducing latency & energy waste.



---

Findings:

ğŸ“ SCHE2MA reduces average service latency by 103.4% compared to centralized RL solutions.
ğŸ“ Energy consumption is reduced by 17.1%, making it a more sustainable alternative.
ğŸ“ Distributed RL improves scalability, enabling large-scale 5G/B5G deployments.
ğŸ“ Avoids single-point failures, improving network reliability.

ğŸ“Œ Advantage Over Previous Papers:
âœ… Combines AI-driven decision-making (Reinforcement Learning) with distributed multi-domain orchestration.
âœ… Outperforms traditional centralized and static SFC placement solutions.
âœ… Optimizes both performance (latency) and cost (energy savings).


